commit.message: build: adjust variables for FindPython usage

Merge pull request #105 from jfpanisset/cmake_python into dev

* jfpanisset/cmake_python:
  Remove CMake conditionals and make FindPython REQUIRED
  Retain backwards compatibility
  Update CMake Python detection

Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <david.aguilar@disneyanimation.com>

Remove CMake conditionals and make FindPython REQUIRED

As per review, partio specifies CMake 3.15 or newer so
backwards compatibility is not required.
Also build should fail if FindPython doesn't find Python.

Signed-off-by: Jean-Francois Panisset <panisset@gmail.com>

Retain backwards compatibility

Signed-off-by: Jean-Francois Panisset <panisset@gmail.com>

Update CMake Python detection

CMake 3.12 adds FindPython which replaces FindPythonInterp
and FindPythonLibs and updates corresponding result variables.
As of CMake 3.27 you must set CMP0148 to OLD to retain this behavior.
This PR updates CMake code to the new behavior while retaining
support for older CMake versions.

Signed-off-by: Jean-Francois Panisset <panisset@gmail.com>

support merging particle sets based on 2 different attributes

See merge request effects/partio!32

support merging particle sets based on 2 different attributes

Previously, you could merge particle sets and override a particle
when the value of a specified attribute (typ. 'ids') was identical.  Because
ids can sometimes be unintentionally duplicated, an additional attribute
can be specified when performing the matching.  When used, a particle is
overridden only when the values of both attributes are identical.

toward: LOOK-1965 Duplicate particle IDs in baked aurora xgenAuroraFiles
